cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.CR

This paper deals with probabilistic logic programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves reasoning with conditional constraints, which is related to logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper presents new entailment relations, which are a fundamental concept in programming languages and semantics (cs.PL). The use of probabilistic reasoning also suggests a connection to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with program transformations for increased efficiency, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
